credit.credit-words: Raag Jog ascending and descending scales (aroh & avroh)
This popular composition in Raag Jog is an old
drut khayal written from the perspective of a woman
Her heart is filled with gladness,
and she urges her friends to join her in singing auspicious songs
and preparing the house for his arrival.
The Musescore-generated audio does not render Indian music accurately.
Raag Jog, especially, involves a lot of glides unique to Indian music.
So please click on the sound-mixer icon and choose the YouTube video as the audio source.
in Raag Jog, Teentaal (16-beat rhythm cycle)
